<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-09-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-09-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="819" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d819">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.2531/32</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-09-30">September 30, 1931</date>.<lb/>[Received
                                October 10.]</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 976</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my telegram No. 119,
                            September 25, 6 p.m., I have the honor to transmit copies of the notes
                            exchanged on September 28 with the Chilean Government on commercial
                            policy (Enclosures Nos. 1 and 2).<note n="8" xml:id="d819fn8"><hi rend="italic">Infra.</hi></note></p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                        <p>After the elections I hope that conditions will be such with the new
                            Government that negotiations for a definite commercial treaty may soon
                            be resumed and I would appreciate appropriate instructions.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">W. S. Culbertson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>